The surveys were aimed at assessing and quantifying the estuarine fish population. A Water Framework Directive compatible beach seine net, deployed from a RIB and hand hauled onto the beach, was used during the surveys in 2013 and 2014. This method is the Environment Agency standard, and therefore allows comparison with EA surveys conducted in adjacent estuaries. </ns0:Summary>    <ns0:Related_URL>       <ns0:URL>http://www.eastern-ifca.gov.uk/</ns0:URL>    </ns0:Related_URL>    <ns0:Metadata_Name>9.4</ns0:Metadata_Name>    <ns0:Metadata_Version>[CEOS IDN DIF]</ns0:Metadata_Version>    <ns0:DIF_Creation_Date>2015-02-25 2015-02-25 2015-02-25</ns0:DIF_Creation_Date> </ns0:DIF>
